  "abstract": "The semi-arid tropics (SAT) are prone to hot summers and erratic rainfall. In such\r\nregions, abiotic stresses such as drought, low temperature and high salinity, are\r\nenvironmental factors that dramatically limit plant growth and crop productivity.\r\nDrought is the chief factor for yield loss in the SAT",
